                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/123: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Piles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-01T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Department’s 40, July 27, 6 p.m. I had an interview with President this
                    afternoon and left with him a copy of note. I referred to opinion of Minister of
                    Industry that decree is not sustainable and to Colombia-Venezuelan arbitration
                    and urged rescission of decree. He seemed impressed and promised a decision
                    early next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
